		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>March 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44; 1860</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I have the pleasure of<lb/> acknowledging the receipt of your favor of<lb/> the <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Ins. enclosing check for &#36;41.50<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> the hands of <persName>Mr Allen</persName>&#44; you<lb/> received I suppose a List from<lb/> <persName>Mr<lb/> Isaacs</persName>.  <add>&#63;</add> his return of money<lb/> collected in the Messengers office amounting<lb/> to &#36;340.20 also &#36;240.60 <del>recd</del> recd<lb/> from sh<add>&#63;</add>  I think this about<lb/> closes our collections</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will oblige me by<lb/> sending on your full Bill now<lb/> for advertising&#44; the last Bill was only up<lb/> to a certain date &#38; is now increased by<lb/> recent advertisement.  Please let<lb/> me have to date &#38; I will remit you<lb/> my check for the amount.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With best respects I remain<lb/> yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Henry I Hart</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phil</placeName></p>
		</body>
